:R-HSA-446193  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006488 ;
        rdfs:comment        "N-linked glycosylation commences with the 14-step synthesis of a dolichol lipid-linked oligosaccharide (LLO) consisting of 14 sugars (2 core GlcNAcs, 9 mannoses and 3 terminal GlcNAcs). This pathway is highly conserved in eukaryotes, and a closely related pathway is found in many eubacteria and Archaea. Mutations in the genes associated with N-glycan precursor synthesis lead to a diverse group of disorders collectively known as Congenital Disorders of Glycosylation (type I and II) (Sparks et al. 1993). The phenotypes of these disorders reflect the important role that N-glycosylation has during development, controlling the folding and the properties of proteins in the secretory pathway, and proteins that mediate cell-to-cell interactions or timing of development." ;
        rdfs:label          "Biosynthesis of the N-glycan precursor (dolichol lipid-linked oligosaccharide, LLO) and transfer to a nascent protein" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Dall'Olio, GM, 2009-11-10" , "Reviewed: Gagneux, P, 2010-04-16" , "Edited: Jassal, B, 2009-11-10" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-446193" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-446203/R-HSA-446203> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

